    title: 'Weapon ability "Unwieldy" — "each model may carry only one Unwieldy item" is now checked',
    description: 'Surfaced 2026-06-08 while cross-checking the Weapon-types/Unique/Unwieldy glossary trio against canonical text. `coreRules.ts` (\'unwieldy\') already carries the verbatim, complete text from Custom40k Core Rules.txt L1447-1449 ("The model does not gain an additional attack for having a pistol in close combat. Each model may carry only one Unwieldy item.") — the glossary entry itself was correct, but the per-model cap had zero enforcement (the string "Unwieldy" appears in 43 data files across nearly every faction\'s armory/units). Fixed by mirroring the existing "Unique" handling exactly: added `isUnwieldyItem(desc)` to `equipMods.ts` (regex `/\\bUnwieldy\\b/`, sibling to `isUniqueItem`), then a new `unwieldyModelBlocked(arm, sec)` in `ArmoryModal.tsx` alongside `uniqueArmyBlocked` — blocks adding a second Unwieldy item by resolving each of the model\'s own `currentArmory` entries back to their `ArmoryItem` (via the existing `findArmoryItem` resolver helper) and checking their `desc` for "Unwieldy". Scoped to the current model\'s own armory (per-model cap), unlike "Unique" which checks the whole army (per-army cap) — matching the canonical text\'s different scope. Wired into `isAddBlocked` so it greys out the option in the picker exactly like Unique/once-per-model do.',
